1
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:11,767
<i> Let me go!</i>

2
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:13,800
<i> You're an animal!</i>

3
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:15,167
<i> Don't worry.</i>

4
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:16,600
<i> I'm a professional.</i>

5
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:17,533
<i> It's Enriquez.</i>

6
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:19,033
<i> Mandong Warak has her.</i>

7
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,800
<i>Sir, just tell us, we're ready
to attack right away.</i>

8
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:22,567
<i>No, no. I'm the only one
who should take action.</i>

9
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:24,500
<i> He wants me to face him alone.</i>

10
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:25,600
<i>The manhunt operation continues.</i>

11
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:27,533
<i>If Conde thinks
this is the best option,</i>

12
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:28,767
<i> let's just trust him.</i>

13
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:31,600
<i> Coordinate with Major Flores.</i>

14
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:35,500
<i>Let's do everything we can
to save your sister, Bobby.</i>

15
00:00:35,667 --> 00:00:37,100
<i> Your boyfriend sent a message.</i>

16
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:38,467
<i> He said he's on his way.</i>

17
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,367
<i> After I kill him,</i>

18
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,600
<i> I'll take you to heaven.</i>

19
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:43,567
<i> You're an animal!</i>

20
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,633
<i>Mando, I'm the one
who wronged you.</i>

21
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:47,700
<i> Let Enriquez go.</i>

22
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:49,300
<i>Do you remember
when you handcuffed me?</i>

23
00:00:49,433 --> 00:00:51,067
<i> You ruined my face!</i>

24
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,833
<i>That's not enough for the number
of police officers you killed.</i>

25
00:00:53,967 --> 00:00:55,133
<i> We're just the same.</i>

26
00:00:55,267 --> 00:00:56,900
<i>The difference is that
you don't get acquitted.</i>

27
00:00:57,033 --> 00:01:00,367
<i>So it's just right that everyone
I killed deserved to be killed!</i>

28
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:03,033
<i>You're the next one on my list.</i>

29
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:13,967
Edgar!

30
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,033
What are you doing here?

31
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,633
I miss you so much, Sweetie.

32
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,033
Did you miss me too?

33
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,367
Oh, by the way, this is for you.

34
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:26,200
Thank you.

35
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:29,100
Oh, what's with you?

36
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:30,900
Aren't you glad I'm here?

37
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:32,133
Of course I am.

38
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:34,100
I just didn't know
you were set free.

39
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,567
Yes, I'm free.

40
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:40,733
Didn't you watch the news?

41
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:42,100
You escaped, Edgar?

42
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:43,733
Don't make any noise.

43
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:46,000
- Someone might hear you.
- Are you crazy?

44
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:47,967
You'll get me in trouble too.

45
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,900
What? No, Hon! No, Hon!

46
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:51,100
Just pack your things.

47
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:53,533
- Pack your things. Go ahead!
- What? Why?

48
00:01:53,667 --> 00:01:55,167
I know, Sweetie,
we were on the rocks last time,

49
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,400
but I'm here now.

50
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:59,367
We can go to a faraway place.

51
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,367
Just the two of us,

52
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,000
so we can live a normal life.

53
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:03,533
Sweetie, I love you so much.

54
00:02:03,667 --> 00:02:05,633
Sweetie, pack your things,
please.

55
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:07,200
Go ahead.

56
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:11,633
But let's play
hide-and-seek first.

57
00:02:11,767 --> 00:02:14,833
If I catch you,

58
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,400
I'll chop you up finely...

59
00:02:18,533 --> 00:02:24,567
while your love team watches.

60
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,100
And then...

61
00:02:26,233 --> 00:02:28,400
I'll kill her next.

62
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:35,667
So now, hide, okay?

63
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,200
I'll count to ten.

64
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:39,933
One...

65
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:43,233
Two...

66
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:47,700
Three...

67
00:02:50,033 --> 00:02:51,100
Four...

68
00:02:53,567 --> 00:02:54,667
Five...

69
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:58,167
Six...

70
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:02,500
Seven!

71
00:03:04,467 --> 00:03:05,433
Eight...

72
00:03:07,767 --> 00:03:08,800
Nine...

73
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,533
Ten.

74
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,767
<i> Tonyo...</i>

75
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:40,300
Tonyo...

76
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,567
<i> Tonyo...</i>

77
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:47,733
Where are you?

78
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:54,067
Tonyo...

79
00:03:55,867 --> 00:03:58,567
You can leave, but...

80
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:02,333
you'll leave
your love team behind.

81
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:07,900
Tonyo...

82
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:16,133
Tonyo...

83
00:04:30,967 --> 00:04:33,333
<i> Tonyo...</i>

84
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,500
<i> Stop!</i>

85
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,933
Sweetie, what's your problem?

86
00:05:28,067 --> 00:05:30,033
Isn't this what we want?

87
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:31,333
Why do you seem...

88
00:05:31,467 --> 00:05:33,167
Why don't you seem
to be in the mood?

89
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,033
I'm just nervous, Edgar.

90
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,833
Sweetie, don't worry.

91
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:38,733
As long as I'm here,

92
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:41,000
no one can hurt us.

93
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,967
I'll protect you,

94
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:45,367
the two of us, okay?

95
00:05:47,667 --> 00:05:50,300
Remember, Bautista...

96
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:54,533
our attack here should be
for interrogation.

97
00:05:54,667 --> 00:05:57,067
Wait. This is it.

98
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:01,100
We're going to talk to
the fugitives' relatives.

99
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:06,467
We need to determine if what
they're saying is true or not.

100
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,600
So...

101
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,600
Why aren't you taking notes?

102
00:06:10,733 --> 00:06:11,933
Why?

103
00:06:12,067 --> 00:06:13,833
This is a free lesson!

104
00:06:13,967 --> 00:06:15,400
Is it necessary, Sir Eric?

105
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:16,667
Of course!

106
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,367
If you want to learn
from the best.

107
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,533
Never mind.

108
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:22,733
Just watch and learn.

109
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,833
Be careful.

110
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,967
Are you expecting someone?

111
00:06:41,133 --> 00:06:42,167
No, no.

112
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:45,067
I think it's the police
officers.

113
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:47,833
Sweetie, tell them
you didn't hear from me.

114
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:49,500
Or I went to Manila
or something.

115
00:06:49,633 --> 00:06:51,900
Okay? Okay? It's up to you,
I'll hide.

116
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,533
Why did it take you so long
to open the door?

117
00:07:01,667 --> 00:07:03,600
Are you ready? Let's go.

118
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:11,500
Excuse me, Sir, but I don't know
Sweetie Villanueva.

119
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:14,000
Maybe she's the previous
tenant here.

120
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,900
Why, Miss?

121
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:17,833
How long have you been
living here?

122
00:07:17,967 --> 00:07:20,833
Almost three years.

123
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:23,233
Where is the village hall here?

124
00:07:23,367 --> 00:07:28,533
Maybe we can ask where we can
find Sweetie Villanueva.

125
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:31,567
Bautista, you're a fast learner.

126
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:34,633
Of course,
I learn from the best!

127
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:36,067
Yes, Miss.

128
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,633
Where is the village hall here?

129
00:07:37,767 --> 00:07:39,100
Simon, let's leave later.

130
00:07:39,233 --> 00:07:41,200
I'm just finishing something.

131
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:42,567
Go ahead, go home first.

132
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,233
Why are you sending me home?

133
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,533
Aren't we supposed
to go somewhere?

134
00:07:45,667 --> 00:07:47,633
Is there a problem?

135
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,633
Simon...

136
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,367
You two are shameless!

137
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,767
You two are shameless!

138
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:57,833
You!

139
00:07:57,967 --> 00:07:59,567
Is this what you're doing to me
while I'm away,

140
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:00,700
while I'm in jail?

141
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,133
- What?
- You're wrong!

142
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:04,067
- It's not like that.
- Hey!

143
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,167
How dare you come here?

144
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,367
I know you're wanted!

145
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,600
I'll call the police!

146
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:11,167
You're crazy!

147
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:14,700
If I go to jail,
It'll be for killing you!

148
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,500
Edgar!

149
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:22,767
- Come back here, Simon! Simon!
- Simon!

150
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,567
Tonyo!

151
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:11,833
Move!

152
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:14,400
Move! Move! Move!

153
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:16,267
Come back here! Hey!

154
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:21,033
There's Edgar Villanueva!
Let's go!

155
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:24,667
Roman, did Mando give you
an update already?

156
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,733
I've been calling him
for a while now,

157
00:09:25,867 --> 00:09:27,367
but he's not answering.

158
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:32,133
Glen...

159
00:09:33,667 --> 00:09:35,433
Dad.

160
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:36,833
Why did you get up?

161
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:38,600
You should be resting.

162
00:09:38,733 --> 00:09:40,033
What?

163
00:09:40,167 --> 00:09:43,367
Have you talked
to the major yet?

164
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,433
What's the update on Bobby?

165
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,633
Yes, yes.

166
00:09:49,767 --> 00:09:51,333
I've talked to him.

167
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:52,867
As of now, they still
don't know

168
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,367
where Sergeant Enriquez is.

169
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:59,100
But they'll get back to us
when they have information.

170
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:01,467
But you, Dad, you have to rest.

171
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:03,867
I'll take you upstairs
so you can rest.

172
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,933
I can't rest!

173
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:08,367
Especially since I know that

174
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:12,700
your sister is in the hands
of the bad guy.

175
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:17,400
Glen, I'm begging you.

176
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:20,100
Please save your sister.

177
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:25,767
Yes, Dad, we'll save Bobby.

178
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,533
Move! Move!

179
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:09,767
- Move aside!
- Come back here!

180
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:11,467
Come back!

181
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:22,100
I'll kill you!

182
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:24,700
- I'll kill you, you animal!
- Move!

183
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:26,333
Stop that!

184
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,067
Let me go!

185
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,767
I'll kill that animal
even if I go to jail!

186
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:32,700
Let me go!

187
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:37,233
You animal!
You're even my friend!

188
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:39,500
Edgar, it's not my fault!

189
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,367
Sweetie came to me herself!

190
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,833
Simon! Simon! Simon!

191
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:47,633
Edgar, that's enough!

192
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,767
I went to him!

193
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,400
I love him!

194
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:56,467
Forgive me, Edgar.

195
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,033
Come here.

196
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:36,767
You thought we wouldn't
catch you, right?

197
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,733
Do you know what case
I'm in jail for?

198
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:41,333
We know, attempted murder.

199
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:43,533
Do you know why?

200
00:13:43,667 --> 00:13:46,500
I almost killed our neighbor...

201
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:49,933
because he and my wife
were flirting.

202
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:52,500
I'm ready to kill
and go to jail,

203
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:54,767
because I love my wife.

204
00:13:56,867 --> 00:13:58,167
But...

205
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:01,233
I've been thinking...

206
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:04,067
I'm fighting
for the wrong woman.

207
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:09,400
Enough of that drama!

208
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,433
Get inside. Get in!

209
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:20,667
I'm fighting
for the wrong woman.

210
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,100
I feel like he's
pertaining to me.

211
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:47,400
Goodbye, Conde.

212
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,433
Sir...

213
00:15:20,567 --> 00:15:21,967
Sir Tonyo...

214
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,500
Sir...

215
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:31,967
Sir...

216
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,667
Mando is gone.

217
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:56,867
Sir, your wound...

218
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,300
No...

219
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:03,500
We can't get him to admit...

220
00:16:03,633 --> 00:16:05,867
who set him free.

221
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:14,700
Are you hurt, Enriquez?

222
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,400
No, Sir, I'm fine.

223
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:20,867
Thank you very much
for saving me.

224
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:23,733
Sir, your wound,

225
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:25,267
we need to take you
to the hospital.

226
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,833
For sure, the stitches
must have opened.

227
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:37,100
You're really stubborn, Bobby!

228
00:16:37,233 --> 00:16:38,700
What did I tell you then?

229
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:41,133
Didn't I tell you not to join
in the search for Mando?

230
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,633
You said yes!

231
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:44,733
But what did you do?

232
00:16:44,867 --> 00:16:45,967
You still looked for him!

233
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,200
Sir, I only did that

234
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,600
because I didn't want Mando
to come after you...

235
00:16:48,733 --> 00:16:51,967
The problem with you, Bobby, is
that you always have a reason!

236
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:54,333
You don't understand
what I'm trying to tell you!

237
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:55,467
Don't you understand?

238
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,900
I don't want you to get hurt.

239
00:16:57,033 --> 00:16:58,633
I'd rather be
the one to get hurt

240
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:00,933
than have you get hurt
by this jerk!

241
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:04,067
The problem with you, Bobby,
is that you're numb!

242
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:06,233
You think you're so good!

243
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:08,700
Okay, fine, you're good!
But what are you going to do?

244
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:10,033
What are you going to do when...

245
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:35,967
Sir, Sir...

246
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:37,400
- They're here, Sir.
- What?

247
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:38,900
- Sir...
- Wait a minute!

248
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:41,367
It'll take some time for them
to come up here.

249
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:13,067
- Here.
- Sir, Sir...

250
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:23,100
He's dead, Sir.

251
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:25,300
De Jesus, call the chief.

252
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:42,933
Hello?

253
00:18:43,067 --> 00:18:44,367
Major?

254
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,800
What's the update?

255
00:18:46,933 --> 00:18:48,667
What?

256
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:51,467
What? Bobby's safe already?

257
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:54,733
Thank you very much, Major!

258
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,967
Yes, thank you, thank you!

259
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:58,933
Okay, okay.

260
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:06,700
Lord...

261
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:12,000
Thank you very much
for saving my daughter.

262
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:15,967
I promise, I'll make it up
to her.

263
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,400
Dad...

264
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:23,767
Dad, are you okay?

265
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:26,833
Glen, your sister
is safe already.

266
00:19:29,367 --> 00:19:30,700
Okay, that's...

267
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:31,633
that's good news,

268
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:33,533
that's good news.

269
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:36,533
So how's Mando?

270
00:19:36,667 --> 00:19:41,000
Did he admit who shamelessly
let him out of prison?

271
00:19:41,133 --> 00:19:43,733
Son, Mando is dead.

272
00:19:43,867 --> 00:19:46,367
No information has been
obtained on him.

273
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:47,933
It doesn't matter anymore, Glen.

274
00:19:48,067 --> 00:19:51,000
What matters is,
your sister is safe,

275
00:19:51,133 --> 00:19:52,967
and she's in the hospital now.

276
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,633
And I'm going to see her.

277
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:56,667
No, no, no, Dad.

278
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,033
Stay here.

279
00:19:58,167 --> 00:20:00,600
You need to rest.

280
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:02,767
I'll go to the hospital
to check on Bobby.

281
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:06,033
After all, she's safe already.

282
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:08,033
Don't be stubborn, Dad, okay?

283
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:11,233
You have to stay here and rest.

284
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:12,467
Okay, Glen.

285
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,700
And I'm sure Bobby
won't be happy

286
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:16,500
when she finds out you almost
suffered a heart attack

287
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:18,567
because of her.

288
00:20:20,067 --> 00:20:21,667
Okay.

289
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:25,600
Go to the hospital.

290
00:20:25,733 --> 00:20:27,200
Just...

291
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:33,667
hug her for me and kiss her,
okay?

292
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,267
Okay.

293
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:37,367
Okay, Dad.

294
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:38,800
But now, you should get
some rest.

295
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:40,600
Go back to your room.

296
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:42,200
Okay.

297
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,833
- Okay, okay.
- Yes, Dad.

298
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:52,333
Get some rest.

299
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,433
Bok...

300
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:11,600
it seems your wound
is getting worse.

301
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:13,933
Yes, Bok.

302
00:21:14,067 --> 00:21:16,367
I've been badly hit.

303
00:21:18,267 --> 00:21:20,533
But it's okay.

304
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:22,833
How about you, Ma'am Bobby?
How are you?

305
00:21:22,967 --> 00:21:24,433
Are you hurt?

306
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:26,567
No...

307
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,433
But I'm ready.

308
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:30,100
What?

309
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:35,133
I mean, I'm ready to go.

310
00:21:35,267 --> 00:21:36,833
Come on, come on.

311
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:38,833
Noble, Torres,
you take care of this.

312
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:40,567
I'm going back to the station.

313
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:43,367
Enriquez, Bok, how about you?

314
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:45,167
- What? No!
- Sir, no!

315
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,467
What?

316
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:50,667
I don't understand you.

317
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:53,733
Sir...

318
00:21:53,867 --> 00:21:55,700
we need to take Tonyo to...

319
00:21:55,833 --> 00:21:57,600
Sir Tonyo to the hospital.

320
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,167
His wound is...

321
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,633
- Come on.
- Let's go.

322
00:22:00,767 --> 00:22:02,400
Let's go, Sir. Let's go.

323
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,167
Bobby...

324
00:22:32,133 --> 00:22:34,333
Thank God you're safe.

325
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:42,800
Dad sent me here
to check up on you.

326
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:44,767
Are you hurt?
Did something happen to you?

327
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:47,967
No, Vice Mayor.
It's okay, I'm okay.

328
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,033
Okay, well, dad will be glad...

329
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:53,833
that nothing bad
happened to you.

330
00:22:53,967 --> 00:22:56,400
Where is Lieutenant Conde?

331
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:59,033
I just want to thank him
also in person.

332
00:22:59,167 --> 00:23:01,667
They're stitching up his wound
again...

333
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,367
because it opened up.

334
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:08,167
Bobby!

335
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:09,700
Sir!

336
00:23:09,833 --> 00:23:12,600
Sir, why did you come out?

337
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:14,767
You're supposed to be resting,
right?

338
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:17,367
Don't be mad.

339
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:19,767
I just really want to see you.

340
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:22,800
Vice Mayor.

341
00:23:22,967 --> 00:23:25,400
Conde, Major Flores told us

342
00:23:25,533 --> 00:23:29,033
about what you did
to save my sister.

343
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:30,433
Thank you so much.

344
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:32,533
Vice Mayor...

345
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:35,400
if it weren't for Bobby,
for sure...

346
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:37,500
something bad would've
happened to me too.

347
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:38,633
I know.

348
00:23:38,767 --> 00:23:40,700
That's why you two are really
good together.

349
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:46,667
I mean, as partners...

350
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,533
because you complement
each other very well.

351
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:53,900
Okay, I'll leave you for now.

352
00:23:54,033 --> 00:23:56,200
I just need to report to dad.

353
00:23:56,367 --> 00:23:57,733
I have a hunch, Conde,

354
00:23:57,867 --> 00:24:00,800
that there is a new mastermind
behind all this.

355
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:02,233
Tonyo, get well soon,

356
00:24:02,367 --> 00:24:04,667
because I need you both.

357
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,700
Calabari needs to be safe.

358
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:07,767
Okay, Vice Mayor.

359
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:08,833
Thank you.

360
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:10,333
Okay.

361
00:24:10,467 --> 00:24:12,867
I'll go ahead.

362
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,100
Thank you, Vice Mayor.

363
00:24:14,233 --> 00:24:15,200
Okay.

364
00:24:16,967 --> 00:24:18,300
You can go ahead, Sir,
I'll take care of him.

365
00:24:18,433 --> 00:24:19,867
Thank you.

366
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:24,967
Sir, you're really so stubborn.

367
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,333
Didn't I tell you not to leave
the room and get some rest?

368
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:29,133
You're stubborn.

369
00:24:31,367 --> 00:24:32,300
Bobby...

370
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:40,300
Bobby...

371
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:43,267
I know I've become stubborn.

372
00:24:44,933 --> 00:24:46,467
I'm sorry.

373
00:24:47,933 --> 00:24:50,967
I just can't stand
not saving you.

374
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:54,567
Something might happen to you,
and I can't take that.

375
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:56,600
So if it's okay with you,

376
00:24:56,733 --> 00:24:59,700
can we start over?

377
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:01,867
Please.

378
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:12,167
I'm going to show the vice mayor
a hula dance!

379
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,500
You don't stand a chance
against these hips.

380
00:25:14,633 --> 00:25:16,833
Why are you so obsessed
with the vice mayor?

381
00:25:16,967 --> 00:25:19,000
That vice mayor is fake.

382
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:20,600
What? Why?

383
00:25:20,733 --> 00:25:22,367
Mayor, I'm following Glen.

384
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:23,900
Can we talk to you?

385
00:25:24,033 --> 00:25:26,633
You said you saw the fugitive
Mateo Ramos in the area.

386
00:25:28,033 --> 00:25:30,533
<i>Ma'am Bobby has accepted
the flowers.</i>

387
00:25:30,667 --> 00:25:33,400
<i> So now, let's all clap.</i>

388
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:34,800
<i>- Hands up!
- Yeah!</i>

389
00:25:34,933 --> 00:25:36,367
<i>- Hands up!
- Oh, yeah!</i>

390
00:25:36,533 --> 00:25:37,600
Does this tickle you?

391
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:38,667
Yes, there!

392
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:40,633
You have no shame!

393
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:41,833
You're so shameless!

394
00:25:41,967 --> 00:25:43,700
You just led me on!
